  "prompt": "Who is the most educated president in the world ?",
  "response": "Determining the \"most educated\" president in the world can be subjective, as educational achievement can vary widely in terms of degrees earned, fields of study, and institutions attended. However, one often cited example of a highly educated president is Franklin D. Roosevelt, who served as the President of the United States from 1933 to 1945. Roosevelt attended Harvard University and later Columbia Law School.\n\nOther notable examples include:\n\n1. **John F. Kennedy (United States)**: Graduated from Harvard University with a Bachelor of Arts in government in 1940.\n2. **Woodrow Wilson (United States)**: Earned a Ph.D. in political science from Johns Hopkins University in 1886.\n3. **Nelson Mandela (South Africa)**: Obtained a law degree from the University of South Africa, along with other legal qualifications earned through the University of London and other institutions.\n\nGlobally, there have been presidents with extensive educational backgrounds. For example:\n\n1. **Draupadi Murmu (India)**: Holds multiple advanced degrees and has educational experience from prestigious Indian institutions.\n2. **Ellen Johnson Sirleaf (Liberia)**: Graduated from Harvard University with a Master of Public Administration degree, becoming the first female African head of state with that qualification.\n\nThese examples highlight a few presidents known for their educational achievements, though this list is far from exhaustive, and many other leaders worldwide have similarly impressive academic credentials.",
